Class LexicalStringComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.zer0bandwidth.android.lib.util.StringComparator.Base
      • net.zer0bandwidth.android.lib.util.LexicalStringComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<java.lang.String>, StringComparator

    public class LexicalStringComparator
extends StringComparator.Base
implements StringComparator
    Sorts strings lexically.

    Algorithm Summary

    1. If String.equals(java.lang.Object) returns true, return 0 quickly.
    2. Search across the strings, comparing the character at each index, and returning a value as soon as a difference is discovered.
    3. If characters at shared indices match, then the longer string is "greater".
    Since:
    zer0bandwidth-net/android 0.2.1 (#56)
